node.text:
@medwed33 wins an historic 2021 US Open Final in three sets against the World Number 1 @djokernole. The Russian tennis champion celebrated the win wearing his @bovet1822 Flying Tourbillon OttantaSei (86 in Italian) designed in collaboration with Pininfarina, one of the most famous car designer. Four sapphire crystals around the 44 mm diameter of the watch allow for the movement to be viewed at every dimension. The tourbillon’s architecture and design increase both the piece’s accuracy and transparency, since its attachments are practically invisible. #Bovet

Limited edition: 86 pieces
Retail price: $ 207,000.00

Photo: @usopen | @bovet1822

node.text:
@jacobandco has unveiled the new $1.5 million dollars Twin Turbo Furious Sapphire, the first ever watch to incorporate a minute repeater inside a sapphire crystal case. The watch comes in 3 models differentiated by a chapter ring that surrounds the dial of each watch: one in red, green and the other in blue (made in collaboration with @bugatti). The sapphire crystal case provides a full view of the complex machinery of the Twin Turbo Furious. This includes all the complications of this high-performance watch inspired by the speed and beauty of hypercars. #JacobandCo

Photo: @jacobandco

node.text:
@djkhaled received as a gift from his wife a @patekphilippe Nautilus Chronograph 5980/1R in 18k rose gold, one of the most sought after timepieces on market. This watch presents a black gradient dial with rose gold applied hour markers and luminescent coating. This masterpiece has been introduced in 2013 following the successful stainless steel version. #PatekPhilippe

Retail price: $97,500.00
Market price: $250,000.00

Photo: @djkhaled | @patekphilippe

node.text:
The king is officially back! @cristiano in his debut for Manchester United scored a brace to led his team to victory. In this shot the football legend was wearing a @rolex GMT-Master II in 18k yellow gold set with blue sapphires, rubies and diamonds. This iconic masterpiece is set with 23 diamonds, 18 blue sapphires, 18 rubies on the bezel as well as 76 brilliant-cut diamonds on the case. Introduced back in 2007 this watch is no longer in production but available in 18k rose gold. #Rolex

Retail price: $88,400.00
Market price: $115,000.00

Photo: @cristiano | @rolex

node.text:
@audemarspiguet has finally unveiled the first Royal Oak ‘Skeleton’ full covered with baguette-cut diamonds. This 18k rose gold timepiece is set with 436 baguette-cut diamonds, illuminating the cutting-edge openworked double balance wheel mechanism in rhodium-toned which is visible on both sides of the watch. After many custom timepieces AP decided to meet the customer needs with this high-jewelry masterpiece, only 3 pieces will be produced with a retail price of $1.4 million dollars. #AudemarsPiguet

Photo: @audemarspiguet

Photo by INSANE LUXURY in Manhattan, New York with @jacobandco, and @alecmonopoly. May be an image of 1 person, wrist watch and text.

node.text:
@alecmonopoly for the first time has been seen wearing his new @jacobandco Astronomia ‘Alec Monopoly’ in 18k rose gold. This piece contains miniature pop characters and images that are staples of Monopoly’s artwork within the iconic Astronomia four-arm vertical movement and its exclusive complications. The sapphire crystal dome and four sapphire crystal windows on the side provide a full view of the artistic and mechanical creations inside. Monopoly says. “This is by far the smallest scale ‘canvas’ I have ever painted”. #JacobandCo

Limited edition: 9 pieces
Retail price: $ 600,000.00

Photo: @jacobandco

node.text:
@jackgrealish of Manchester City ahead of his latest match for the England National team was wearing a @patekphilippe Nautilus 5740 Perpetual Calendar in 18k white gold. Introduced as the first grand complication in the Nautilus collection, it features a blue sunburst dial with gold applied hour markers and luminescent coating. Thanks to the famous ultra-thin caliber 240 Q movement, this watch is Patek Philippe’s thinnest perpetual calendar. #PatekPhilippe

Retail price: $ 126,850.00
Market price: $ 225,000.00

Photo: @england | @patekphilippe

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by INSANE LUXURY in Manhattan, New York with @champagnepapi, and @jacobandco. May be an image of 1 person, wrist watch and text that says '173 기'.

node.text:
Drake's 'Certified Lover Boy' has now sold over 500,000 units in the US, making it the first album to reach this milestone in under a week in 2021, in this shot he was wearing a @jacobandco Astronomia ‘Casino’ Tourbillon in 18k rose gold. This masterpiece is the first grand complication timepiece with a roulette wheel that spins, allowing the owners to play their favorite game of chance at any time. At the press of the button at 8 o’clock position of the case, the roulette wheel is forcefully spun, sending the little white ceramic ball flying. One of the 18 pieces produced is owned by @thenotoriousmma . #JacobandCo

Limited edition: 18 pieces
Retail price: $ 620,000.00

Photo: @gettyimages | @jacobandco

node.text:
The Italian motorcycle racer @andreaiannone wears a limited @geraldcharles_official Maestro GC3.0 in rose gold with green ‘emerald’ dial, part of brand’s Premier 2021. This timepiece is powered by an hand finished ultra-thin automatic chronograph movement called GCA3022/12 made by Vaucher. The case back of the watch shows the limited edition number engraved and the words ‘Premier 2021’ lasered on the sapphire crystal. #GeraldCharles

Limited edition: 25 pieces
Retail price: $ 43,000.00

Photo: @_marc_lucas | @geraldcharles_official

node.text:
@platinumtimesco has now available an exclusive @richardmille RM055 Automatic ‘Asia Edition’ made in partnership with the golfer Bubba Watson. This 30-piece limited edition is made in ceramic and was available only for the Asian market. It features a skeletonized movement with a caramel inner bezel and rose gold colored hands with luminous hour markers. #RichardMille

Photo: @platinumtimesco
